1
00:00:00,291 --> 00:00:02,043
<i>Previously on </i>Heroes...

2
00:00:03,878 --> 00:00:05,922
- Get out of my head.
- This is a dream.

3
00:00:06,172 --> 00:00:08,883
- It's not a dream!
- I came to take you out of here.

4
00:00:09,133 --> 00:00:10,969
In the dream, Emma, my friend...

5
00:00:11,219 --> 00:00:13,179
You save her
before she kills thousands.

6
00:00:13,346 --> 00:00:15,015
You really think you can get us out?

7
00:00:15,265 --> 00:00:16,391
Let me see you try.

8
00:00:17,225 --> 00:00:20,687
Charlie was my heart, my world,
my happily ever after.

9
00:00:20,937 --> 00:00:23,481
I did everything I could
to try and save her life.

10
00:00:23,731 --> 00:00:25,191
Where is Charlie?

11
00:00:25,441 --> 00:00:28,319
I'm the only one who knows exactly
where your sweet Charlie is.

12
00:00:28,737 --> 00:00:30,530
- Help him.
- It's our intent to prove

13
00:00:30,697 --> 00:00:32,031
that he abused his power

14
00:00:32,198 --> 00:00:35,452
to bend space and time
selfishly and repeatedly.

15
00:00:36,161 --> 00:00:38,538


16
00:00:39,205 --> 00:00:41,916


17
00:00:43,626 --> 00:00:46,171
Showing my dad's memories
is gonna enlighten me?

18
00:00:46,421 --> 00:00:49,382
- Don't do this.
- You're afraid she'll see the real you?

19
00:00:49,966 --> 00:00:51,801
- You brought a gun.
- I was scared.

20
00:00:51,968 --> 00:00:53,303
First time you ever killed.

21
00:00:53,470 --> 00:00:55,805
You actually thought
that I would turn on him?

22
00:00:56,431 --> 00:00:58,725
Claire Bennet needs some time
to think about my offer.

23
00:01:03,938 --> 00:01:06,608
It's time to gather the family.
We're moving on to bigger things.

24
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:08,485
The greatest show we've ever done.

25
00:01:11,237 --> 00:01:12,238
Dad?

26
00:01:14,491 --> 00:01:15,492
I'm here.

27
00:01:16,201 --> 00:01:17,285
No signal.

28
00:01:19,579 --> 00:01:20,997
- You okay?
- Yeah. You?

29
00:01:21,372 --> 00:01:23,374
Yeah, help me get these ropes off.

30
00:01:25,001 --> 00:01:26,503
A lantern over there?

31
00:01:34,844 --> 00:01:36,012
We're buried.

32
00:01:36,262 --> 00:01:39,808
- How far down we are?
- It felt like we dropped 40 or 50 feet.

33
00:01:41,893 --> 00:01:43,102
Can anyone hear us?

34
00:01:43,686 --> 00:01:44,813
Anybody hear us?

35
00:01:55,198 --> 00:01:56,199
Help!

36
00:01:56,616 --> 00:01:57,992
Can anybody hear us?

37
00:02:00,119 --> 00:02:02,330
- Anybody up there?
- Somebody help us!

38
00:02:04,290 --> 00:02:06,084
Help!
Can anybody hear us?

39
00:02:06,543 --> 00:02:07,919
Can you hear us out there?

40
00:02:34,028 --> 00:02:37,991
Subtitles: Rebel (1.0)
www.sous-titres.eu

41
00:03:21,534 --> 00:03:22,744
How long has it been?

42
00:03:24,746 --> 00:03:26,456
Half a day, maybe.

43
00:03:27,498 --> 00:03:29,459
Feels like we were in there
for years.

44
00:03:32,337 --> 00:03:35,507
- Is your buddy Samuel here with you?
- Came alone this time...

45
00:03:36,507 --> 00:03:37,508
so to speak.

46
00:03:38,176 --> 00:03:40,762
- What do you want?
- Samuel asked me to make sure

47
00:03:40,929 --> 00:03:43,264
your friends downstairs
aren't a problem for us.

48
00:03:43,932 --> 00:03:45,308
I guess that means you too.

49
00:03:50,938 --> 00:03:52,732
Sorry to break up the lovefest.

50
00:03:56,110 --> 00:03:57,111
Come on.

51
00:03:59,405 --> 00:04:00,740
You're having doubts.

52
00:04:01,658 --> 00:04:03,952
Look at you.
Come on, I can tell.

53
00:04:04,202 --> 00:04:05,537
You don't want to do this.

54
00:04:06,913 --> 00:04:08,456
What I want doesn't matter.

55
00:04:10,041 --> 00:04:11,084
I have no choice.

56
00:04:11,793 --> 00:04:14,212
Don't bother.
We got you outnumbered.

57
00:04:17,173 --> 00:04:19,133
<i>You want to leave, right now.</i>

58
00:04:21,803 --> 00:04:23,596
Are you trying to push a thought?

59
00:04:24,806 --> 00:04:27,183
All but one of us are pretty...
thoughtless.

60
00:04:36,943 --> 00:04:40,613
Tonight will be a night
unlike any other.

61
00:04:41,656 --> 00:04:42,657
Tonight...

62
00:04:44,367 --> 00:04:46,661
we change everything.

63
00:04:48,079 --> 00:04:52,000
We've been shamed into believing
we're second-class citizens.

64
00:04:54,002 --> 00:04:55,753
When the truth is,
we're king of the hill!

65
00:04:57,964 --> 00:05:00,758
They should aspire to be like us,
not the other way around.

66
00:05:01,259 --> 00:05:02,343
That's right.

67
00:05:03,511 --> 00:05:05,388
And so I make this pledge to you.

68
00:05:07,223 --> 00:05:08,224
Tonight...

69
00:05:10,018 --> 00:05:11,310
once and for all...

70
00:05:12,311 --> 00:05:16,149
we pull back the curtain
and reveal ourselves for who we are.

71
00:05:18,735 --> 00:05:21,112
After tonight, we will be...

72
00:05:21,988 --> 00:05:23,448
respected.

73
00:06:01,652 --> 00:06:02,653
Come on!

74
00:06:03,279 --> 00:06:05,698
Don't.
Think about what you're doing.

75
00:06:07,492 --> 00:06:08,618
Don't do this!

76
00:06:13,748 --> 00:06:14,582
Don't!

77
00:06:20,755 --> 00:06:21,631
You okay?

78
00:06:24,884 --> 00:06:25,718
Sit.

79
00:06:29,722 --> 00:06:30,723
Just dislocated.

80
00:06:31,349 --> 00:06:32,183
Awesome.

81
00:06:36,479 --> 00:06:37,981
What the hell is he doing here?

82
00:06:54,413 --> 00:06:55,122


83
00:06:55,289 --> 00:06:56,207
There you are.

84
00:06:56,666 --> 00:06:57,792
Time for your solo.

85
00:06:59,085 --> 00:07:00,795


86
00:07:01,462 --> 00:07:03,506
How do you think
all the people are gonna find us?

87
00:07:04,048 --> 00:07:05,550
You're gonna bring them here.

88
00:07:07,051 --> 00:07:10,221
I told you you had a unique gift.
It's time to put it to use.

89
00:07:12,723 --> 00:07:13,891


90
00:07:14,183 --> 00:07:15,184
What dream?

91
00:07:15,685 --> 00:07:17,895


92
00:07:18,229 --> 00:07:19,564


93
00:07:21,440 --> 00:07:23,234
Thousands of people will die.

94
00:07:27,572 --> 00:07:29,240
He was right about you.

95
00:07:32,869 --> 00:07:34,579
You disappoint me, Emma.

96
00:07:35,371 --> 00:07:37,749
You can't force me to do anything.

97
00:07:43,087 --> 00:07:46,424
I would have preferred
you were a willing participant,

98
00:07:47,383 --> 00:07:48,801
but these things happen.

99
00:07:50,803 --> 00:07:52,388
She's all yours, Mr. Doyle.

100
00:07:52,555 --> 00:07:54,390
I've always had a thing...

101
